                'answer' => '{"en":"<p>No. There is no &ldquo;free&rdquo; aluminum in the zeolite; it is part of the molecular structure of the zeolite. This form of aluminum is totally inert and does not interact with the body in any way, as proven in numerous studies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This is further demonstrated in our third-party tested chemical analysis, where the zeolite cage was dissolved using a strong acid mixture called Aqua Regia, and shows the chemical constituent of aluminum. However the chemical analysis of the finished product, which shows what is bioavailable, shows NO available aluminum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The molecular structure of zeolite is indestructible in the body. Zeolites are neither water nor fat soluble, and the molecule can withstand high heat.<\\/p>","pl":"<p>Nie. W zeolicie nie ma \\"wolnego\\" aluminium; jest cz\\u0119\\u015bci\\u0105 struktury molekularnej zeolitu. Ta forma aluminium jest ca\\u0142kowicie oboj\\u0119tna i w \\u017caden spos&oacute;b nie wsp&oacute;\\u0142dzia\\u0142a z cia\\u0142em, co potwierdzaj\\u0105 liczne badania.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Zosta\\u0142o to dodatkowo wykazane w naszej analizie chemicznej przeprowadzonej przez niezale\\u017cn\\u0105 firm\\u0119, w kt&oacute;rej klatk\\u0119 zeolitow\\u0105 rozpuszczono stosuj\\u0105c mocn\\u0105 mieszanin\\u0119 kwas&oacute;w o nazwie Aqua Regia i kt&oacute;ra pokazuje sk\\u0142adnik chemiczny aluminium. Jednak analiza chemiczna gotowego produktu, kt&oacute;ry pokazuje, co jest biodost\\u0119pne, pokazuje brak dost\\u0119pnego aluminium.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Struktura molekularna zeolitu jest niezniszczalna w ciele. Zeolity nie s\\u0105 ani rozpuszczalne w wodzie, ani w t\\u0142uszczu, a cz\\u0105steczka mo\\u017ce wytrzyma\\u0107 wysokie temperatury.<\\/p>","jp":"<p>No. There is no &ldquo;free&rdquo; aluminum in the zeolite; it is part of the molecular structure of the zeolite. This form of aluminum is totally inert and does not interact with the body in any way, as proven in numerous studies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This is further demonstrated in our third-party tested chemical analysis, where the zeolite cage was dissolved using a strong acid mixture called Aqua Regia, and shows the chemical constituent of aluminum. However the chemical analysis of the finished product, which shows what is bioavailable, shows NO available aluminum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The molecular structure of zeolite is indestructible in the body. Zeolites are neither water nor fat soluble, and the molecule can withstand high heat.<\\/p>","ja":"<p>No. There is no &ldquo;free&rdquo; aluminum in the zeolite; it is part of the molecular structure of the zeolite. This form of aluminum is totally inert and does not interact with the body in any way, as proven in numerous studies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This is further demonstrated in our third-party tested chemical analysis, where the zeolite cage was dissolved using a strong acid mixture called Aqua Regia, and shows the chemical constituent of aluminum. However the chemical analysis of the finished product, which shows what is bioavailable, shows NO available aluminum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The molecular structure of zeolite is indestructible in the body. Zeolites are neither water nor fat soluble, and the molecule can withstand high heat.<\\/p>","es":"<p>No. There is no &ldquo;free&rdquo; aluminum in the zeolite; it is part of the molecular structure of the zeolite. This form of aluminum is totally inert and does not interact with the body in any way, as proven in numerous studies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This is further demonstrated in our third-party tested chemical analysis, where the zeolite cage was dissolved using a strong acid mixture called Aqua Regia, and shows the chemical constituent of aluminum. However the chemical analysis of the finished product, which shows what is bioavailable, shows NO available aluminum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The molecular structure of zeolite is indestructible in the body. Zeolites are neither water nor fat soluble, and the molecule can withstand high heat.<\\/p>","th":"<p>No. There is no &ldquo;free&rdquo; aluminum in the zeolite; it is part of the molecular structure of the zeolite. This form of aluminum is totally inert and does not interact with the body in any way, as proven in numerous studies.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This is further demonstrated in our third-party tested chemical analysis, where the zeolite cage was dissolved using a strong acid mixture called Aqua Regia, and shows the chemical constituent of aluminum. However the chemical analysis of the finished product, which shows what is bioavailable, shows NO available aluminum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The molecular structure of zeolite is indestructible in the body. Zeolites are neither water nor fat soluble, and the molecule can withstand high heat.<\\/p>"}',
